'''Emeraz''' is a [[social networking service]] to connect people in the music industry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businesspost.ie/#!story/Home/News/Startup+of+the+day%3A+Emeraz/id/19410615-5218-5097-8262-1edb59700966 |title=Startup Of The Day}}</ref>

== History ==

Emeraz was founded in [[Dublin|Dublin, Ireland]] in 2010, by producer and sound engineer, Stephen Brett.{{citation needed|date=June 2013}} Emeraz originally started out as a place to [[Collaboration|collaborate]] online and [[copyright]] music. In September 2012 a new version of Emeraz launched and is now a complete [[social networking]] platform.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://siliconrepublic.com/start-ups/item/29010-tech-start-up-of-the-week |title=Start-Up Of The Week}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.musictech.net/2013/06/emeraz-the-next-big-thing-officially-launches/|title=Officially Launches}}</ref>

== Features ==

Users of Emeraz are able to collaborate with other musicians and present songs to well-known artists and producers, as well as getting feedback from leading names in the industry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.musictech.net/2013/05/emeraz-the-next-big-thing/|title=Next Big Thing}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://jamsphere.com/product-reviews/emeraz-facebook-for-musicians-launches|title=-'Facebook For Musicians'-}}</ref>

