'''''Marx's Theory of Ideology''''' is a 1982 book about [[Karl Marx]] by the political theorist [[Bhikhu Parekh]]. The work was inspired by Parekh's experience of racial discrimination in British society.<ref name="Times">[[#Tim00|Times Higher Education 2000]].</ref>

==Reception==
''Marx's Theory of Ideology'' was reviewed by Nicholas Abercrombih in ''[[Sociology (journal)|Sociology]]''.<ref>[[#Abe82|Abercrombih 1982]]. pp. 629-630.</ref> The political theorist [[Terrell Carver]], writing in an appendix to the 1995 edition of ''[[Karl Marx: His Life and Environment]]'', called the book a classic exposition of the Marxist theory of ideology.<ref name="Carver">[[#Car95|Carver 1995]]. p. 214.</ref>

